"{\"uid\": \"nypost.com-2024-07-26-entertainment-savannah-guthrie-left-hot-and-bothered-by-2024-paris-olympics-opening-ceremony-threesome-moment\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Savannah Guthriewas feeling a little \\\"hot and bothered\\\" after a segment in theParis 2024 Summer Olympics Opening Ceremonythat gave heavy m\\u00e9nage \\u00e0 trois energy.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 159, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are transitioning from the 'liberty' portion, which got us a little hot and bothered in the pouring rain,\\\" theTodayshow host, 52, said with a wry smile during the Olympics broadcast on Friday, July 26, referencing one of three sections of the opening ceremonies that paid homage to the national motto of France: libert\\u00e9, \\u00e9galit\\u00e9, fraternit\\u00e9 - liberty, equality, fraternity.\", \"from\": 161, \"to\": 538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 469, \"end\": 475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999999992058747, \"rank\": 5.6044629810400695e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The pre-taped bit showed three dancers in a library passing a book called, \\\"Le Triomphe De L'Amour,\\\" which translates to \\\"The Triumph of Love.\\\"\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 683, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After leaving the library, the colorfully dressed group spilled onto the streets of Paris before rushing up a spiral staircase.\", \"from\": 685, \"to\": 812, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 769, \"end\": 774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.8210897369979895e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One person at the center almost kissed each of their friends before they hurried into an apartment and began making out and nuzzling one another.\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 958, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But before things got any steamier, one person looked directly at the camera with a devilish smile and shut the door, leaving the rest to the audience's imagination.\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 1125, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are uninvited, well, OK,\\\" Kelly Clarkson quipped.\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1180, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1157, \"end\": 1171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Clarkson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kelly Clarkson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Clarkson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Clarkson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That was just rude.\\\"\", \"from\": 1181, \"to\": 1202, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The official Olympics account on X, formerly known as Twitter, posted a photo of the three revelers with a quote from Victor Hugo: \\\"The freedom to love is no less sacred than the freedom to think.\\\"\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1401, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1258, \"end\": 1265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.463258852087662e-20, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Providing some context about why the segment may have been included in the show, NBC Olympics primetime host Mike Tirico explained that \\\"the artistic director, Thomas Jolly, decided to lean into some of the clich\\u00e9s about France.\\\"\", \"from\": 1403, \"to\": 1632, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1484, \"end\": 1496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBC Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\"}, {\"begin\": 1512, \"end\": 1523, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Tirico\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mike Tirico\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Tirico\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Tirico\"}, {\"begin\": 1563, \"end\": 1569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9981192156010329, \"rank\": 0.0018829310042424502, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}, {\"begin\": 1624, \"end\": 1630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999999992058747, \"rank\": 5.6044629810400695e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He added, \\\"The City of Light, known as a romantic city.\", \"from\": 1634, \"to\": 1689, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So much literature written or set here involves love.\", \"from\": 1690, \"to\": 1743, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So in this segment, love and literature the twain shall meet.\", \"from\": 1744, \"to\": 1805, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Or maybe we should say trois.\\\"\", \"from\": 1806, \"to\": 1836, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The broadcasters' reactions were not lost on those watching at home.\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1906, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They literally just showed a m\\u00e9nage \\u00e0 trois in the Olympic opening ceremony and the NBC team had no idea how to react lmfaoooooo,\\\"one person postedon social media before adding, \\\"VIVE LA FRANCE.\\\"\", \"from\": 1908, \"to\": 2104, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1993, \"end\": 1996, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.or